7413 // Emit an extension from a GR64 to a GR128. ClearEven is true
7414 // if the high register of the GR128 value must be cleared or false if
7415 // it's "don't care".
7416 MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitExt128(MachineInstr &MI,
7417  MachineBasicBlock *MBB,
7418  bool ClearEven) const {
7419  MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
7420  const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
7421  static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
7422  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
7423  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
7424 
7425  Register Dest = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
7426  Register Src = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
7427  Register In128 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::GR128BitRegClass);
7428 
7429  BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF), In128);
7430  if (ClearEven) {
7431  Register NewIn128 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::GR128BitRegClass);
7432  Register Zero64 = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::GR64BitRegClass);
7433 
7434  BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::LLILL), Zero64)
7435  .addImm(0);
7436  BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG), NewIn128)
7437  .addReg(In128).addReg(Zero64).addImm(SystemZ::subreg_h64);
7438  In128 = NewIn128;
7439  }
7440  BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG), Dest)
7441  .addReg(In128).addReg(Src).addImm(SystemZ::subreg_l64);
7442 
7443  MI.eraseFromParent();
7444  return MBB;
7445 }
7446 
7447 MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitMemMemWrapper(
7448  MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, unsigned Opcode) const {
7449  MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
7450  const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
7451  static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
7452  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
7453  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
7454 
7455  MachineOperand DestBase = earlyUseOperand(MI.getOperand(0));
7456  uint64_t DestDisp = MI.getOperand(1).getImm();
7457  MachineOperand SrcBase = earlyUseOperand(MI.getOperand(2));
7458  uint64_t SrcDisp = MI.getOperand(3).getImm();
7459  uint64_t Length = MI.getOperand(4).getImm();
7460 
7461  // When generating more than one CLC, all but the last will need to
7462  // branch to the end when a difference is found.
7463  MachineBasicBlock *EndMBB = (Length > 256 && Opcode == SystemZ::CLC ?
7464  splitBlockAfter(MI, MBB) : nullptr);
7465 
7466  // Check for the loop form, in which operand 5 is the trip count.
7467  if (MI.getNumExplicitOperands() > 5) {
7468  bool HaveSingleBase = DestBase.isIdenticalTo(SrcBase);
7469 
7470  Register StartCountReg = MI.getOperand(5).getReg();
7471  Register StartSrcReg = forceReg(MI, SrcBase, TII);
7472  Register StartDestReg = (HaveSingleBase ? StartSrcReg :
7473  forceReg(MI, DestBase, TII));
7474 
7475  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &SystemZ::ADDR64BitRegClass;
7476  Register ThisSrcReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
7477  Register ThisDestReg = (HaveSingleBase ? ThisSrcReg :
7478  MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC));
7479  Register NextSrcReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
7480  Register NextDestReg = (HaveSingleBase ? NextSrcReg :
7481  MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC));
7482 
7483  RC = &SystemZ::GR64BitRegClass;
7484  Register ThisCountReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
7485  Register NextCountReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
7486 
7487  MachineBasicBlock *StartMBB = MBB;
7488  MachineBasicBlock *DoneMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
7489  MachineBasicBlock *LoopMBB = emitBlockAfter(StartMBB);
7490  MachineBasicBlock *NextMBB = (EndMBB ? emitBlockAfter(LoopMBB) : LoopMBB);
7491 
7492  // StartMBB:
7493  // # fall through to LoopMMB
7494  MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
7495 
7496  // LoopMBB:
7497  // %ThisDestReg = phi [ %StartDestReg, StartMBB ],
7498  // [ %NextDestReg, NextMBB ]
7499  // %ThisSrcReg = phi [ %StartSrcReg, StartMBB ],
7500  // [ %NextSrcReg, NextMBB ]
7501  // %ThisCountReg = phi [ %StartCountReg, StartMBB ],
7502  // [ %NextCountReg, NextMBB ]
7503  // ( PFD 2, 768+DestDisp(%ThisDestReg) )
7504  // Opcode DestDisp(256,%ThisDestReg), SrcDisp(%ThisSrcReg)
7505  // ( JLH EndMBB )
7506  //
7507  // The prefetch is used only for MVC. The JLH is used only for CLC.
7508  MBB = LoopMBB;
7509 
7510  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), ThisDestReg)
7511  .addReg(StartDestReg).addMBB(StartMBB)
7512  .addReg(NextDestReg).addMBB(NextMBB);
7513  if (!HaveSingleBase)
7514  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), ThisSrcReg)
7515  .addReg(StartSrcReg).addMBB(StartMBB)
7516  .addReg(NextSrcReg).addMBB(NextMBB);
7517  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), ThisCountReg)
7518  .addReg(StartCountReg).addMBB(StartMBB)
7519  .addReg(NextCountReg).addMBB(NextMBB);
7520  if (Opcode == SystemZ::MVC)
7521  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PFD))
7522  .addImm(SystemZ::PFD_WRITE)
7523  .addReg(ThisDestReg).addImm(DestDisp + 768).addReg(0);
7524  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(Opcode))
7525  .addReg(ThisDestReg).addImm(DestDisp).addImm(256)
7526  .addReg(ThisSrcReg).addImm(SrcDisp);
7527  if (EndMBB) {
7528  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
7529  .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_ICMP).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_NE)
7530  .addMBB(EndMBB);
7531  MBB->addSuccessor(EndMBB);
7532  MBB->addSuccessor(NextMBB);
7533  }
7534 
7535  // NextMBB:
7536  // %NextDestReg = LA 256(%ThisDestReg)
7537  // %NextSrcReg = LA 256(%ThisSrcReg)
7538  // %NextCountReg = AGHI %ThisCountReg, -1
7539  // CGHI %NextCountReg, 0
7540  // JLH LoopMBB
7541  // # fall through to DoneMMB
7542  //
7543  // The AGHI, CGHI and JLH should be converted to BRCTG by later passes.
7544  MBB = NextMBB;
7545 
7546  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::LA), NextDestReg)
7547  .addReg(ThisDestReg).addImm(256).addReg(0);
7548  if (!HaveSingleBase)
7549  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::LA), NextSrcReg)
7550  .addReg(ThisSrcReg).addImm(256).addReg(0);
7551  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::AGHI), NextCountReg)
7552  .addReg(ThisCountReg).addImm(-1);
7553  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::CGHI))
7554  .addReg(NextCountReg).addImm(0);
7555  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
7556  .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_ICMP).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_NE)
7557  .addMBB(LoopMBB);
7558  MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
7559  MBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
7560 
7561  DestBase = MachineOperand::CreateReg(NextDestReg, false);
7562  SrcBase = MachineOperand::CreateReg(NextSrcReg, false);
7563  Length &= 255;
7564  if (EndMBB && !Length)
7565  // If the loop handled the whole CLC range, DoneMBB will be empty with
7566  // CC live-through into EndMBB, so add it as live-in.
7567  DoneMBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
7568  MBB = DoneMBB;
7569  }
7570  // Handle any remaining bytes with straight-line code.
7571  while (Length > 0) {
7572  uint64_t ThisLength = std::min(Length, uint64_t(256));
7573  // The previous iteration might have created out-of-range displacements.
7574  // Apply them using LAY if so.
7575  if (!isUInt<12>(DestDisp)) {
7576  Register Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::ADDR64BitRegClass);
7577  BuildMI(*MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(SystemZ::LAY), Reg)
7578  .add(DestBase)
7579  .addImm(DestDisp)
7580  .addReg(0);
7581  DestBase = MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, false);
7582  DestDisp = 0;
7583  }
7584  if (!isUInt<12>(SrcDisp)) {
7585  Register Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&SystemZ::ADDR64BitRegClass);
7586  BuildMI(*MBB, MI, MI.getDebugLoc(), TII->get(SystemZ::LAY), Reg)
7587  .add(SrcBase)
7588  .addImm(SrcDisp)
7589  .addReg(0);
7590  SrcBase = MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, false);
7591  SrcDisp = 0;
7592  }
7593  BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(Opcode))
7594  .add(DestBase)
7595  .addImm(DestDisp)
7596  .addImm(ThisLength)
7597  .add(SrcBase)
7598  .addImm(SrcDisp)
7599  .setMemRefs(MI.memoperands());
7600  DestDisp += ThisLength;
7601  SrcDisp += ThisLength;
7602  Length -= ThisLength;
7603  // If there's another CLC to go, branch to the end if a difference
7604  // was found.
7605  if (EndMBB && Length > 0) {
7606  MachineBasicBlock *NextMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
7607  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
7608  .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_ICMP).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_CMP_NE)
7609  .addMBB(EndMBB);
7610  MBB->addSuccessor(EndMBB);
7611  MBB->addSuccessor(NextMBB);
7612  MBB = NextMBB;
7613  }
7614  }
7615  if (EndMBB) {
7616  MBB->addSuccessor(EndMBB);
7617  MBB = EndMBB;
7618  MBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
7619  }
7620 
7621  MI.eraseFromParent();
7622  return MBB;
7623 }
7624 
7625 // Decompose string pseudo-instruction MI into a loop that continually performs
7626 // Opcode until CC != 3.
7627 MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitStringWrapper(
7628  MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, unsigned Opcode) const {
7629  MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
7630  const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
7631  static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
7632  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
7633  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
7634 
7635  uint64_t End1Reg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
7636  uint64_t Start1Reg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg();
7637  uint64_t Start2Reg = MI.getOperand(2).getReg();
7638  uint64_t CharReg = MI.getOperand(3).getReg();
7639 
7640  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = &SystemZ::GR64BitRegClass;
7641  uint64_t This1Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
7642  uint64_t This2Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
7643  uint64_t End2Reg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
7644 
7645  MachineBasicBlock *StartMBB = MBB;
7646  MachineBasicBlock *DoneMBB = splitBlockBefore(MI, MBB);
7647  MachineBasicBlock *LoopMBB = emitBlockAfter(StartMBB);
7648 
7649  // StartMBB:
7650  // # fall through to LoopMMB
7651  MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
7652 
7653  // LoopMBB:
7654  // %This1Reg = phi [ %Start1Reg, StartMBB ], [ %End1Reg, LoopMBB ]
7655  // %This2Reg = phi [ %Start2Reg, StartMBB ], [ %End2Reg, LoopMBB ]
7656  // R0L = %CharReg
7657  // %End1Reg, %End2Reg = CLST %This1Reg, %This2Reg -- uses R0L
7658  // JO LoopMBB
7659  // # fall through to DoneMMB
7660  //
7661  // The load of R0L can be hoisted by post-RA LICM.
7662  MBB = LoopMBB;
7663 
7664  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), This1Reg)
7665  .addReg(Start1Reg).addMBB(StartMBB)
7666  .addReg(End1Reg).addMBB(LoopMBB);
7667  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::PHI), This2Reg)
7668  .addReg(Start2Reg).addMBB(StartMBB)
7669  .addReg(End2Reg).addMBB(LoopMBB);
7670  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), SystemZ::R0L).addReg(CharReg);
7671  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(Opcode))
7672  .addReg(End1Reg, RegState::Define).addReg(End2Reg, RegState::Define)
7673  .addReg(This1Reg).addReg(This2Reg);
7674  BuildMI(MBB, DL, TII->get(SystemZ::BRC))
7675  .addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_ANY).addImm(SystemZ::CCMASK_3).addMBB(LoopMBB);
7676  MBB->addSuccessor(LoopMBB);
7677  MBB->addSuccessor(DoneMBB);
7678 
7679  DoneMBB->addLiveIn(SystemZ::CC);
7680 
7681  MI.eraseFromParent();
7682  return DoneMBB;
7683 }
7684 
7685 // Update TBEGIN instruction with final opcode and register clobbers.
7686 MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitTransactionBegin(
7687  MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, unsigned Opcode,
7688  bool NoFloat) const {
7689  MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
7690  const TargetFrameLowering *TFI = Subtarget.getFrameLowering();
7691  const SystemZInstrInfo *TII = Subtarget.getInstrInfo();
7692 
7693  // Update opcode.
7694  MI.setDesc(TII->get(Opcode));
7695 
7696  // We cannot handle a TBEGIN that clobbers the stack or frame pointer.
7697  // Make sure to add the corresponding GRSM bits if they are missing.
7698  uint64_t Control = MI.getOperand(2).getImm();
7699  static const unsigned GPRControlBit[16] = {
7700  0x8000, 0x8000, 0x4000, 0x4000, 0x2000, 0x2000, 0x1000, 0x1000,
7701  0x0800, 0x0800, 0x0400, 0x0400, 0x0200, 0x0200, 0x0100, 0x0100
7702  };
7703  Control |= GPRControlBit[15];
7704  if (TFI->hasFP(MF))
7705  Control |= GPRControlBit[11];
7706  MI.getOperand(2).setImm(Control);
7707 
7708  // Add GPR clobbers.
7709  for (int I = 0; I < 16; I++) {
7710  if ((Control & GPRControlBit[I]) == 0) {
7711  unsigned Reg = SystemZMC::GR64Regs[I];
7712  MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, true, true));
7713  }
7714  }
7715 
7716  // Add FPR/VR clobbers.
7717  if (!NoFloat && (Control & 4) != 0) {
7718  if (Subtarget.hasVector()) {
7719  for (int I = 0; I < 32; I++) {
7720  unsigned Reg = SystemZMC::VR128Regs[I];
7721  MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, true, true));
7722  }
7723  } else {
7724  for (int I = 0; I < 16; I++) {
7725  unsigned Reg = SystemZMC::FP64Regs[I];
7726  MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, true, true));
7727  }
7728  }
7729  }
7730 
7731  return MBB;
7732 }
7733 
7734 MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::emitLoadAndTestCmp0(
7735  MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB, unsigned Opcode) const {
7736  MachineFunction &MF = *MBB->getParent();
7737  MachineRegisterInfo *MRI = &MF.getRegInfo();
7738  const SystemZInstrInfo *TII =
7739  static_cast<const SystemZInstrInfo *>(Subtarget.getInstrInfo());
7740  DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
7741 
7742  Register SrcReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg();
7743 
7744  // Create new virtual register of the same class as source.
7745  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(SrcReg);
7746  Register DstReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(RC);
7747 
7748  // Replace pseudo with a normal load-and-test that models the def as
7749  // well.
7750  BuildMI(*MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(Opcode), DstReg)
7751  .addReg(SrcReg)
7752  .setMIFlags(MI.getFlags());
7753  MI.eraseFromParent();
7754 
7755  return MBB;
7756 }

7758 MachineBasicBlock *SystemZTargetLowering::EmitInstrWithCustomInserter(
7759  MachineInstr &MI, MachineBasicBlock *MBB) const {
7760  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
7761  case SystemZ::Select32:
7762  case SystemZ::Select64:
7763  case SystemZ::SelectF32:
7764  case SystemZ::SelectF64:
7765  case SystemZ::SelectF128:
7766  case SystemZ::SelectVR32:
7767  case SystemZ::SelectVR64:
7768  case SystemZ::SelectVR128:
7769  return emitSelect(MI, MBB);
7770 
7771  case SystemZ::CondStore8Mux:
7772  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STCMux, 0, false);
7773  case SystemZ::CondStore8MuxInv:
7774  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STCMux, 0, true);
7775  case SystemZ::CondStore16Mux:
7776  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STHMux, 0, false);
7777  case SystemZ::CondStore16MuxInv:
7778  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STHMux, 0, true);
7779  case SystemZ::CondStore32Mux:
7780  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STMux, SystemZ::STOCMux, false);
7781  case SystemZ::CondStore32MuxInv:
7782  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STMux, SystemZ::STOCMux, true);
7783  case SystemZ::CondStore8:
7784  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STC, 0, false);
7785  case SystemZ::CondStore8Inv:
7786  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STC, 0, true);
7787  case SystemZ::CondStore16:
7788  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STH, 0, false);
7789  case SystemZ::CondStore16Inv:
7790  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STH, 0, true);
7791  case SystemZ::CondStore32:
7792  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::ST, SystemZ::STOC, false);
7793  case SystemZ::CondStore32Inv:
7794  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::ST, SystemZ::STOC, true);
7795  case SystemZ::CondStore64:
7796  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STG, SystemZ::STOCG, false);
7797  case SystemZ::CondStore64Inv:
7798  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STG, SystemZ::STOCG, true);
7799  case SystemZ::CondStoreF32:
7800  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STE, 0, false);
7801  case SystemZ::CondStoreF32Inv:
7802  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STE, 0, true);
7803  case SystemZ::CondStoreF64:
7804  return emitCondStore(MI, MBB, SystemZ::STD, 0, false);
7805  case SystemZ::CondStoreF64Inv:

7807 
7808  case SystemZ::PAIR128:

7812  case SystemZ::ZEXT128:

7815  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_SWAPW:
7816  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, 0, 0);
7817  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_SWAP_32:
7818  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, 0, 32);
7819  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_SWAP_64:
7820  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, 0, 64);
7821 
7822  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_AR:
7823  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AR, 0);
7824  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_AFI:
7825  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AFI, 0);
7826  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AR:
7827  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AR, 32);
7828  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AHI:
7829  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AHI, 32);
7830  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AFI:
7831  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AFI, 32);
7832  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AGR:
7833  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AGR, 64);
7834  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AGHI:
7835  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AGHI, 64);
7836  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_AGFI:
7837  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::AGFI, 64);
7838 
7839  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_SR:
7840  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::SR, 0);
7841  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_SR:
7842  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::SR, 32);
7843  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_SGR:
7844  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::SGR, 64);
7845 
7846  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_NR:

7914 
7915  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_NRi:

7917  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOADW_NILHi:
7918  return emitAtomicLoadBinary(MI, MBB, SystemZ::NILH, 0, true);
7919  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_LOAD_NRi:

7982  case SystemZ::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAPW:
7983  return emitAtomicCmpSwapW(MI, MBB);
7984  case SystemZ::MVCSequence:
7985  case SystemZ::MVCLoop:
7986  return emitMemMemWrapper(MI, MBB, SystemZ::MVC);
7987  case SystemZ::NCSequence:
7988  case SystemZ::NCLoop:
7989  return emitMemMemWrapper(MI, MBB, SystemZ::NC);
7990  case SystemZ::OCSequence:
7991  case SystemZ::OCLoop:
7992  return emitMemMemWrapper(MI, MBB, SystemZ::OC);
7993  case SystemZ::XCSequence:

7996  case SystemZ::CLCSequence:

7999  case SystemZ::CLSTLoop:
8000  return emitStringWrapper(MI, MBB, SystemZ::CLST);
8001  case SystemZ::MVSTLoop:
8002  return emitStringWrapper(MI, MBB, SystemZ::MVST);
8003  case SystemZ::SRSTLoop:
8004  return emitStringWrapper(MI, MBB, SystemZ::SRST);
8005  case SystemZ::TBEGIN:
8006  return emitTransactionBegin(MI, MBB, SystemZ::TBEGIN, false);
8007  case SystemZ::TBEGIN_nofloat:
8008  return emitTransactionBegin(MI, MBB, SystemZ::TBEGIN, true);
8009  case SystemZ::TBEGINC:
8010  return emitTransactionBegin(MI, MBB, SystemZ::TBEGINC, true);
8011  case SystemZ::LTEBRCompare_VecPseudo:

8013  case SystemZ::LTDBRCompare_VecPseudo:
8014  return emitLoadAndTestCmp0(MI, MBB, SystemZ::LTDBR);
8015  case SystemZ::LTXBRCompare_VecPseudo:
8016  return emitLoadAndTestCmp0(MI, MBB, SystemZ::LTXBR);
8017 
8018  case TargetOpcode::STACKMAP:
8019  case TargetOpcode::PATCHPOINT:
8020  return emitPatchPoint(MI, MBB);
8021 
8022  default:
8023  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected instr type to insert");
8024  }
8025 }
